-- Cosan, Grupo Elektra, Banco Continental, OGX: Latin America Equity Preview
-- Andres R. Martinez
-- 2010-07-06T08:14:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-06/cosan-grupo-elektra-banco-continental-ogx-latin-america-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Latin American trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses and share prices reflect the previous close.  
 The  MSCI Latin America Index  fell 0.9 percent to 3,677.57.
In Brazil, preferred shares usually are the most-traded class of
stock.  
 Argentina  
 Mirgor SACIFIA  (MIRG AF): Automobile production in
Argentina rose 46.6 percent in June from a year earlier to
65,256 vehicles, the country’s Automakers Association said. The
car parts manufacturer was unchanged at 70.5 pesos.  
 Brazil  
 Cosan Ltd.  (CZLT11 BS): Sugar output in Brazil’s Center
South, the world’s biggest producing region, rose 31 percent in
the first half of June, industry association Unica said. The
parent company of Cosan SA Industria e Comercio rose 3.8 percent
to 18.47 reais.  
 OGX Petroleo e Gas Participacoes  (OGXP3 BZ): The oil
company controlled by Brazilian billionaire  Eike Batista  began
drilling at the Parnaiba Basin in onshore Brazil. OGX rose 0.3
percent to 17.75 reais.  
 Mexico  
 Grupo Elektra SA  (ELEKTRA* MM): The company’s banking unit
may increase the number of ATMs it operates, El Universal
newspaper reported. Grupo Elektra rose 1.4 percent to 512.47
pesos.  
 Peru  
 Banco Continental SA  (CONTINC1 PE): Peruvian corporate bond
sales fell more than 20 percent last month after the central
bank raised the benchmark lending rate twice, Scotiabank Peru
said. The local unit of Spain’s Banco Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria
SA fell 0.3 percent to 6.58 soles.  
